The paper deals with the technical challenges of implementing HTTPS as the default means of connecting to web servers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of various factors on the problem, such as the client's browser and locale, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE), social and information networks (cs.SI), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
